text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: We don't want judges making policy
because policy is inherently political.

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: Policy making presents a series of
Hobson's choices. The straight and
narrow puts folks between a rock
and a hard place, so we have to
sweeten the pot through half-assed
horse-trading.

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: You can't declare that something is
just. You have to make the sausage.
The process is messy, but the end
product is acceptable to the masses.
And courts should respect that.

text.title: Horse Edwards
text.tspan: I confess I'm a little unnerved by
how quickly you went from
horse-trading to sausage-making.

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: That's why horses don't make policy.
Cite as: Andrew Fong, Law of the Horse, TORT BUNNIES (November 7, 2011), http://tortbunnies.com/131.html.
